    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="530"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2630</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1916</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I enclose a proposed telegram
                    to Mr. Gerard.<note n="52" xml:id="d530fn1">For the telegram as sent, see <ref
                            target="frus1916Supp#pg_252">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1916, supp., p.
                        252</ref>.</note> While I am not disposed to unduly press the German
                    Government for an answer to our note, I feel that we should let that <pb
                        facs="0631" n="563" xml:id="pg_563"/> Government know that we are becoming
                    impatient at the delay, which would seem to indicate that they intend to avoid a
                    frank declaration. I also thought it would be well to furnish Gerard with our
                    idea as to the rules which should govern the conduct of naval operations against
                    merchant vessels.</p>
                <p>I would be very much pleased for any changes or suggestions which you may desire
                    to make, and also your views as to the advisability of sending a telegram like
                    the enclosed.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
